WEBVTT

00:00:00.151 --> 00:00:03.632
Conflict is inevitable, but it is not always negative.

00:00:04.293 --> 00:00:10.535
When managed constructively, it maintains optimum stimulation and drives adaptive capabilities.

00:00:11.216 --> 00:00:15.517
Team breakdowns can be understood through a collapsing pyramid of dysfunctions.

00:00:16.178 --> 00:00:20.439
The foundation is an absence of trust where true feelings are hidden.

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:28.523
This immediately sparks the second dysfunction, a fear of conflict leading to artificial harmony.

00:00:29.366 --> 00:00:33.955
Without productive debate, there is a lack of commitment and ambiguity.

00:00:34.596 --> 00:00:42.331
This causes an avoidance of accountability and ultimately inattention to results where ego overrides collective success.
